===Etymology 1===
From {{etyl|enm|en}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|butere||butter|lang=ang}}, from {{etyl|gem-pro|en}} {{m|gem-pro|*buterǭ||butter}} (compare {{etyl|fy|-}} {{term|buter|lang=fy}}, {{etyl|nl|-}} {{term|boter|lang=nl}}, {{etyl|de|-}} {{term|Butter|lang=de}}), from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|būtȳrum|lang=la}}, from {{etyl|grc|en}} {{m|grc|βούτῡρον||cow cheese}}, compound of {{term|sc=polytonic|βοῦς|lang=grc||ox, cow}} and {{m|grc|τῡρός||cheese}}, from {{etyl|xsc|en}}.

Compare {{etyl|ae|-}} {{term|𐬌𐬭𐬌𐬏𐬙||lang=ae|tr=tūiri|curdled milk, whey}}), from {{etyl|ine-pro|en}} {{m|ine-pro|*tuHrós}} (compare [[Middle Indic]] {{term|||tr=tūra|cheese|lang=und}}, {{etyl|ru|-}} {{term|творо́г||curds, soft cheese|lang=ru}}, {{etyl|ang|-}} {{term|lang=ang|þweran||to churn}}, {{term|geþweor||curds|lang=ang}}).

